# TASK_PACKET

Task ID
CRUSHR-FORMAT-15

Title
Harden mirrored dictionaries with generation identity and implement factored namespace dictionaries

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Promote the winning dictionary architecture by (1) making mirrored dictionary copies self-identifying and generation-aware, and (2) replacing full-path dictionary entries with a factored namespace representation that reduces redundant path storage while preserving current recovery guarantees.

This packet exists because FORMAT-14A established that:

- `extent_identity_path_dict_header_tail` is the leading candidate
- single-dictionary placement is too fragile for the lead format
- header+tail mirrored dictionaries preserve named recovery when one copy is lost
- both-copy loss correctly falls back to anonymous recovery
- conflicting copies are detected and fail closed

The remaining work is to make the winning design:
- more precise about dictionary identity/conflict/staleness
- smaller by factoring repeated namespace structure

This is a bounded hardening + optimization packet.
It is not a broad redesign.

